.TH "do_drive_set_taskfiles" 9 "do_drive_set_taskfiles" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
do_drive_set_taskfiles \- write the drive taskfile settings from _GTF
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" do_drive_set_taskfiles
.BI "(ide_drive_t *drive "  ","
.BI "unsigned int gtf_length "  ","
.BI "unsigned long gtf_address "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "drive" 12
the drive to which the taskfile command should be sent
.IP "gtf_length" 12
total number of bytes of _GTF taskfiles
.IP "gtf_address" 12
location of _GTF taskfile arrays
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Write {gtf_address, length gtf_length} in groups of
REGS_PER_GTF bytes.
